sect1.para:
Parameters and properties annotated with @CookieParam, 
@HeaderParam, @MatrixParam, @PathParam, or 
@QueryParam are represented as strings in a raw HTTP request. The specification
says that any of these injected parameters can be converted to an object if the object's class has
a valueOf(String) static method or a constructor that takes one Stringparameter.
In the following, for example,

